---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout title="Getting Started - Helpmaton">
  <Header />
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-white p-8 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="border-2 border-black p-8 mb-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold uppercase mb-4">GETTING STARTED</h1>
        <p class="text-lg opacity-75 mb-2">
          Your journey to AI agent mastery starts here
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm opacity-60 italic">
          (Don't worry, we'll hold your hand)
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <section class="border-2 border-black p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-4xl">1Ô∏è‚É£</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase">Create Your Account</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 opacity-90">
            First things first - sign up for your free 7-day trial. No credit card required, we're not monsters.
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm opacity-90 ml-4">
            <li>Click the "START YOUR 7-DAY TRIAL" button on the homepage</li>
            <li>Enter your email address and create a password</li>
            <li>Verify your email (check your spam folder, we're friendly!)</li>
            <li>You're in! Welcome to the future üöÄ</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <a href="https://app.helpmaton.com" class="inline-block border-2 border-black bg-black px-4 py-2 text-white font-bold uppercase hover:bg-accent hover:border-accent transition-colors text-sm">
              Sign Up Now ‚Üí
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="border-2 border-black p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-4xl">2Ô∏è‚É£</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase">Create Your First Workspace</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 opacity-90">
            Workspaces are like boxes where your AI agents live. Each workspace has its own settings, credits, and team members.
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm opacity-90 ml-4">
            <li>After logging in, click "Create Workspace"</li>
            <li>Give it a name (be creative! Or not, we won't judge)</li>
            <li>Set your spending limits (optional, but recommended)</li>
            <li>Invite team members if you want (also optional)</li>
            <li>Click "Create" and boom! You have a workspace üì¶</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="border-2 border-black p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-4xl">3Ô∏è‚É£</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase">Create Your First Agent</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 opacity-90">
            Now for the fun part - creating your first AI agent! This is where the magic happens.
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm opacity-90 ml-4">
            <li>Navigate to your workspace</li>
            <li>Click "Create Agent"</li>
            <li>Give your agent a name and personality</li>
            <li>Configure what your agent can do (its capabilities)</li>
            <li>Set up any initial instructions or prompts</li>
            <li>Click "Create" and watch your agent come to life! ü§ñ</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm opacity-75 italic">
            Pro tip: Start simple! You can always add more complexity later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="border-2 border-black p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-4xl">4Ô∏è‚É£</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase">Upload Documents</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 opacity-90">
            Give your agents knowledge by uploading documents. They'll read and learn from everything you give them.
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm opacity-90 ml-4">
            <li>Go to the "Documents" section in your workspace</li>
            <li>Click "Upload Document"</li>
            <li>Select your file (PDF, TXT, DOCX, and more)</li>
            <li>Organize documents into folders if needed</li>
            <li>Your agents can now access this knowledge! üìö</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm opacity-75">
            Supported formats: PDF, TXT, DOCX, MD, CSV, and more!
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="border-2 border-black p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-4xl">5Ô∏è‚É£</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase">Test Your Agent</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 opacity-90">
            Time to see your agent in action! Test it out and make sure everything works as expected.
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm opacity-90 ml-4">
            <li>Go to your agent's page</li>
            <li>Use the test interface to send a message</li>
            <li>Watch your agent respond (it's like magic, but real!)</li>
            <li>Adjust settings if needed</li>
            <li>Repeat until you're happy ‚ú®</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="border-2 border-black p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-4xl">6Ô∏è‚É£</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase">Set Up Webhooks (Optional)</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 opacity-90">
            Connect your agent to the real world with webhooks. This lets your agent send and receive messages from external systems.
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm opacity-90 ml-4">
            <li>Go to "Webhooks" in your workspace settings</li>
            <li>Click "Create Webhook"</li>
            <li>Enter your endpoint URL</li>
            <li>Configure which events should trigger the webhook</li>
            <li>Test it out! üîó</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm opacity-75 italic">
            This step is optional - you can always add webhooks later!
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="border-2 border-black p-6 bg-accent text-white">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold uppercase mb-4">üéâ You're All Set!</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 opacity-90">
            Congratulations! You've created your first workspace, agent, and uploaded documents. You're officially a Helpmaton pro!
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4 opacity-90">
            Want to learn more? Check out our full documentation or join our community.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
            <a href="/documentation" class="inline-block border-2 border-white bg-white text-accent px-4 py-2 font-bold uppercase hover:bg-transparent hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm">
              Full Documentation
            </a>
            <a href="/api-reference" class="inline-block border-2 border-white bg-transparent text-white px-4 py-2 font-bold uppercase hover:bg-white hover:text-accent transition-colors text-sm">
              API Reference
            </a>
            <a href="https://discord.gg/NrdE8h83W9" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block border-2 border-white bg-transparent text-white px-4 py-2 font-bold uppercase hover:bg-white hover:text-accent transition-colors text-sm">
              Join Discord
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

